          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Kim Bennett Horvath: <a href="http://www.solasalonstudios.com" target="_blank">Sola Salon Studios</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              Kim Bennett Horvath's passion as a hairdresser has taken her on a journey through the beauty industry for 25 years. As a licensed cosmetologist since the age of 18, she has continued to catapult her career and her business from her humble small town beginnings, and is dedicated to inspiring others in the beauty industry.
              <br><br>
              As a Senior National Educator for Paul Mitchell for the past 23 years she was one of the first Artistic Color Coordinators chosen to help launch Paul Mitchell's first color line, as well as being a Task Force Leader where she trained and coached regional Paul Mitchell National Educators. She received the Paul Mitchell Focus Award in 2012, and continues to educate and help salons grow their business.
              <br><br>
              While working in all aspects of traditional salons, Kim made the decision of salon ownership after meeting Sola's co-founders, Matt and Stratton, at a coffee shop in Denver, Colorado. Kim quickly became the first Sola Professional in early 2004! Throughout her 11+ years at Sola, Kim has supported and represented Sola Salon Studios in myriad ways and in early 2014 became Sola's Director of Education. Within this role, Kim uses her expertise to share the Sola Salon Studios culture to connect and build relationships throughout the Professional Beauty Industry. 
              <br><br>
              Her passion and success as a Sola Professional has spread like wildfire being asked to speak with industry leaders on better business practices and has been featured in many publications including Modern Salon, Behind the Chair, and Milady Pro. She was also recently recognized as a Role Model by American Salon. Kim is dedicated to creating education opportunities for Sola Professionals to inspire them to become successful business owners while also enjoying their best artistic self.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Terri Cowan: <a href="http://www.professionalsalonconcepts.com/" target="_blank">Professional Salon Concepts</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              <em>Innovation! Education! Commitment!</em> These are often the words used by those in the hair care industry to describe Terri Cowan. Terri alongside her husband, Steve Cowan own Professional Salon Concepts, the first beauty industry distributor to earn a place among Inc. Magazine's top 500 privately owned companies in America. They earned this honor not just once, but twice. They were named Modern Salon's “Distributor of the Year” and presented the Diamond Award for Excellence in Customer Service by American Salon Magazine.
              <br><br>
              As proud distributors, Terri and Steve have applied their background and experiences in business and training to build PSC into the industry leader that it is today.
              <br><br>
              Terri serves as one of the Salon Industry's leading and most respected speakers and trainers.  Her direct common sense approach to measuring and quantifying extraordinary customer service, combined with her undeniable sense of humor, is what her audiences enjoy the most. 
              <br><br>
              Today, Terri and Steve Cowan act as consultants to many of the salons they serve. They are consultants for A Robert Cromeans Salons and are combining efforts with John Paul Mitchell Systems to spread their culture. In 2007 they started their journey into the world of the Paul Mitchell Schools.  Today they are Co-Owners to the Paul Mitchell schools in Escanaba, Michigan, Chicago, IL and Lombard, IL.   
              <br><br>
              So their mission continues – &quot;To Grow the Beauty Industry, One Hairdresser at a time.&quot;
            </div>
